   1 # -*- coding=utf-8 -*-
   2 from __future__ import absolute_import, unicode_literals
   3 
   4 from functools import partial
   5 
   6 __all__ = ["partialmethod"]
   7 
   8 
   9 class partialmethod(object):
  10     """Method descriptor with partial application of the given arguments
  11     and keywords.
  12     Supports wrapping existing descriptors and handles non-descriptor
  13     callables as instance methods.
  14     """
  15 
  16     def __init__(self, func, *args, **keywords):
  17         if not callable(func) and not hasattr(func, "__get__"):
  18             raise TypeError("{!r} is not callable or a descriptor".format(func))
  19 
  20         # func could be a descriptor like classmethod which isn't callable,
  21         # so we can't inherit from partial (it verifies func is callable)
  22         if isinstance(func, partialmethod):
  23             # flattening is mandatory in order to place cls/self before all
  24             # other arguments
  25             # it's also more efficient since only one function will be called
  26             self.func = func.func
  27             self.args = func.args + args
  28             self.keywords = func.keywords.copy()
  29             self.keywords.update(keywords)
  30         else:
  31             self.func = func
  32             self.args = args
  33             self.keywords = keywords
  34 
  35     def __repr__(self):
  36         args = ", ".join(map(repr, self.args))
  37         keywords = ", ".join("{}={!r}".format(k, v) for k, v in self.keywords.items())
  38         format_string = "{module}.{cls}({func}, {args}, {keywords})"
  39         return format_string.format(
  40             module=self.__class__.__module__,
  41             cls=self.__class__.__qualname__,
  42             func=self.func,
  43             args=args,
  44             keywords=keywords,
  45         )
  46 
  47     def _make_unbound_method(self):
  48         def _method(*args, **keywords):
  49             call_keywords = self.keywords.copy()
  50             call_keywords.update(keywords)
  51             if len(args) > 1:
  52                 cls_or_self, rest = args[0], tuple(args[1:])
  53             else:
  54                 cls_or_self = args[0]
  55                 rest = tuple()
  56             call_args = (cls_or_self,) + self.args + tuple(rest)
  57             return self.func(*call_args, **call_keywords)
  58 
  59         _method.__isabstractmethod__ = self.__isabstractmethod__
  60         _method._partialmethod = self
  61         return _method
  62 
  63     def __get__(self, obj, cls):
  64         get = getattr(self.func, "__get__", None)
  65         result = None
  66         if get is not None:
  67             new_func = get(obj, cls)
  68             if new_func is not self.func:
  69                 # Assume __get__ returning something new indicates the
  70                 # creation of an appropriate callable
  71                 result = partial(new_func, *self.args, **self.keywords)
  72                 try:
  73                     result.__self__ = new_func.__self__
  74                 except AttributeError:
  75                     pass
  76         if result is None:
  77             # If the underlying descriptor didn't do anything, treat this
  78             # like an instance method
  79             result = self._make_unbound_method().__get__(obj, cls)
  80         return result
  81 
  82     @property
  83     def __isabstractmethod__(self):
  84         return getattr(self.func, "__isabstractmethod__", False)
